Hungarian Picks Pole Vault Title 
Hungarian Istvan Bagyula cleared 5.70 meters to win the men's pole
vault title at the World University Games here on Thursday.
The Hungarian title-winning performance was 10 centimeters away from
the games record.
American Lawrence Johson cleared 5.60 meters to win the silver medal as
Portuguese Nuno Fernandes got the bronze at 5.55.
